      <div type="edition" xml:lang="okz-Latn">
        <p>
<lb n="1"/><g type="gomutraInitial">.</g> <g type="ddandaHooked">.</g> Oṁ siddhi svasti jaya lābha kṣema r̥ddhi 
<lb n="2"/>Oṁ kṣāhā Indrāya svāhā Oṁ ma<lb break="no" n="3"/>ṇipadme hūṁ cortta man· yaja<lb break="no" n="4"/>māna vraḥ kaṁmrateṅ· Añ· <unclear>moṁ</unclear>
<lb n="5"/>nu vraḥ kaṁmrateṅ· Añ· dai<lb n="6"/>ya nu dvipada catuppada R̥<lb break="no" n="7"/>ddhi ru candra ta gi śukr̥<lb break="no" n="8"/><gap quantity="1" reason="illegible" unit="line"/>
            </p>
      </div>
      <div type="apparatus"></div>
      <div source="bib:Pou2001_01" type="translation" xml:lang="fra">
        <p n="1-3">Oṁ, succès, bonheur, victoire, profit, paix, puissance ! Oṁ, <foreign>kṣāhā</foreign>, <foreign>indrāya</foreign>, <foreign>svāha</foreign> ! Oṁ, à Maṇipadma ! Hūṁ, <foreign>cortta</foreign> !</p>
        <p n="3-6">Le donateur <supplied reason="subaudible">étant</supplied> V. K. A. Moṁ, et le dieu est empli de compassion envers les bipèdes, les quadrupèdes.</p>
        <p n="7">Puissance surnaturelle comme celle de Candra <gap reason="illegible"/></p>
      </div>
